<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step16_SemaphoreSlim"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 16 - SemaphoreSlim">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step16ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 16: SemaphoreSlim &amp; Async Throttling"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">THROTTLING: Controlling how many async operations run at the same time.

SemaphoreSlim is like a bouncer at a club: the club has max capacity.
When full, new arrivals wait outside. When someone leaves, the next enters.

Use WaitAsync() for async-friendly locking (the "lock" keyword blocks threads).
SemaphoreSlim(1, 1) acts as an async mutex: only one task at a time.
SemaphoreSlim(N, N) allows up to N concurrent operations.

Common use: Downloading 100 files but limiting to 3 simultaneous connections
to avoid overwhelming the server or running out of sockets.</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? No throttling (all tasks at once)"
                    Command="{Binding NoThrottlingCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? With throttling (max 3 concurrent)"
                    Command="{Binding WithThrottlingCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Async lock (SemaphoreSlim as mutex)"
                    Command="{Binding AsyncLockCommand}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="300"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
